features.text: #Building the worlds first art collection leveraged for the perpetual funding of artistic creation

The launch of ArtDAO Collection 001 

A tokenised collection of 1/1 works by leading up & coming artists from around Lisbon. Collectively owned, governed and grown through 
@sznsNFT
 

$ARTLIS

It’s clear that there’s a big problem with the art world, very few artists make it and those that do are dependent upon a wealthy elite and a small handful of galleries who extract hefty commissions (50%+) and almost all of the speculative upside of their efforts.

 The nature of NFTs offer us a new paradigm in which to rethink this relationship and move towards a world in which all of us can begin to share in both the financial upside of art and a more deep and meaningful relationship to the artists and works being created around us

This collection is the beginning of an experiment in realising that vision. One which places artists at the foundation; bringing them and their works together, and distributing governance over the future development of that collection to them through our $ARTLIS token.

Understanding that artists also need to pay rent, our launch event allows them to sell a % of their $ARTLIS tokens to those wanting to buy into the collection. Bringing them into the community and bridging new relationships between artists and the capital they need.

By leveraging communities over pandering to a wealthy few, we are able to scale and decentralise operations as a DAO at significantly lower costs, allowing ArtDAO to take just 25% in commission with the remainder returned to the artists and curators contributing.

#Created by 003FA1

The collection grows over time through further acquisitions of works agreed upon by the token holders and artists, becoming a living reflection and core aspect of the art scene over time.

ArtDAO re-invests in the artistic community through the provision of studio spaces, events and materials to create a virtuous cycle which grows both the value of the $ARTLIS collection and the artistic wealth and possibilities for the local community and artists here in Lisbon
